Recording the process can sometimes take away from...the process. Art making is intimate so much of the time, it's okay to unplug and just be in the moment. 😘

I am so humbled and honored to be trusted with the stories and experiences of so many people! These are a few of the commissions I have completed over the last few months, and it has been an incredible journey to be able to make art that reflects community and the many facets of what makes us who we are. Painting portraits has been my dream, and it started with myself, facing the wounds from the past and looking forward, hoping to create a space for my children, family, and community to thrive. When we see ourselves being celebrated, we can help others celebrate themselves, too. I see you. I appreciate you.  And I love you.  Thank you all for allowing me the space to make art and trusting me with something so special. ✨️

So, I decided to paint my love and I as a surprise for Valentine's day. In true Crystal fashion, I started late and finished it this morning (it's hard to surprise someone you're with all the time)! We are celebrating 10 years this year, and my art is what got his attention in the first place, so a painting to commemorate our amor is fitting. 🥰
If you've been following me for a while, I'm sure you've seen the different types of work I create... but damn making some juicy, Voluptuous, realistic fleshy paintings are my absolute favorite and I'm glad this piece called me to make it. Thank you for supporting me in my endeavors all these years, @anestivega. I love you and look forward to so many more paintings and adventures as we navigate this wild life 😘😘😘

One day a while back, I was sitting at my vanity doing my makeup. No one was around, so I was in the zone (as I tend to be when I'm making art or doing my makeup)... As I was finishing up, my partner walked in the room and saw me all dolled up. It wasn't a special occasion, I just felt like trying out a new pallette I had... I seemed to take him by surprise as he looked at me in admiration and said "wowwww," before embracing me from behind, leaning in to kiss me on the neck, and go back to what he was working on. In that moment, I half opened my eyes and saw our reflection in the vanity mirror. A soft, passionate moment to remind each other that we still have that desire and intimacy was reflected back at me and I couldn't help but ask him to stay in that position so I could capture that picture just for me. When he walked away and I saw the image saved in my phone, I knew that someday soon this would be in my artwork in some form. 
When valentines day came around, I knew it was time to make this piece and do my best to capture that magic I felt on that day. I worked on it in the early morning and times he wasn't home to make sure he would fully be taken aback by this special work. The day I gave it to him, I also decided to post it on social media, giving yall a glimpse of what I feel love is. Thank you for being here yall, and if you made it this far, thank you for taking time to read this. I appreciate it! 
Viva el amor!

🌼 GIVEAWAY 🌼

 

I’m excited to partner with author V. Castro and Del Rey Books on an empowering sweepstakes to celebrate the release of The Haunting of Alejandra! One lucky winner will receive a hardcover copy of this brand-new literary horror novel, a custom pair of earrings that I created (inspired by the book), two herbal and flower remedies for ancestral connection and dream work, and a set of Wholeness Cards!

 

In The Haunting of Alejandra, a woman is haunted by La Llorona, the vengeful and murderous mother of Mexican legend. And she will not leave until Alejandra follows her mother, her grandmother, and all the women who came before her into the darkness. But Alejandra has inherited more than just their pain. She has inherited the strength and courage of her foremothers.

 

Help banish La Llorona forever with this empowering collection of prizes! The link to enter is in my stories and highlights. 
 

NO PURCHASE NECESSARY. Enter between 4/21/23 and 4/30/23. Open to US residents, 18+. 

 

#thehauntingofalejandra #vcastro #bookgiveaway #booksweeps #sweepstakes #giveaway #crystalgalindoart #delreybooks

 

The earrings are in layers, representing Alejandra's ancestors passing down their ties to La Llorona. The tears drop from each eye at the top layer, a symbol of past generational trauma and sadness. But, they are slowed down by the roses below, marking Alejandra's delicate strength and blossoming hope to break the generational curse, shown in the galactic tears at the bottom.

Reposting in honor of May 5th, #mmiw red dress day.
This piece is a tribute to the Missing and Murdered Indigenous Womxn of the Americas, from Canada to South America. The Red Hand over her mouth is a symbol of the many  women and girls whose voices were taken by violence. It's a  marking used by those who aim to spread awareness and bring justice. The double-headed snake and heart symbols represent the Aztec mother Goddess Coatlicue, as I imagine this calaca would invoke her strength and power to protect the souls of the muxeres whose lives have been tragically taken. The pink and red chiffon represents the missing and murdered muxeres of Juarez. May their souls find peace and comfort and may their loved ones get the closure they deserve. 
"Muertita Divina" 2020 
Crystal Galindo.

It doesn't always have to be about buying our work! 
Although that also helps 😅

1. Share our work! This can help us reach new audiences and even gain new collectors, opportunities, etc. 

2. Like our posts. This tells the algorithm so many of us depend on that our posts need to be shown to even more people. I know it sucks to depend on social media, but at the same time, so many of us have built our audience and support this way cause of how ACCESSIBLE it is. 

3. Tell others about us! If you wear our gear or have our artwork hanging in your home, give a shout out 🥰 

4. Buy our work if you can. 🥰🥰🥰

It's been rough for everyone lately, so here is something you can do to help out artists on Social Media (without spending a dime) 

1. Make an independent post with our work in it (and credit/tag us)
It will send new folks our way! 

2. Share our work in your stories! Even a simple post share takes a few seconds and means the world to us! 

3. Save our post! It shows the algie that people are interested and that will show our posts to more people. 

4. Interact with us! Commenting or tagging your friends in our comments section is such a great way to help. 

5. Keep our names in yallz mouths! Hahahha! If our work interests you and we have a website or newsletter, sign up 💜
